g compile API drift. I need to ensure the output is valid JSON without any markdown and can incorporate arrays. I'm unsure if \\\"deterministic_setup\\\" should be absent or simply empty since the shape allows for an array.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra setup is needed. org.apache.maven:maven-core:2.0.7 resolves its required Maven, Plexus, Wagon, and ClassWorlds dependencies transitively; meaningful coverage is reachable with in-process APIs such as diagnostics, runtime information, lifecycle/plugin classes, and MavenCli help/version paths. The observed javac failure is due to Maven 2.0.7 constructor signature drift in maven-artifact exceptions, not a missing dependency, Docker service, environment variable, or system property.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No required environment variables or system properties. If tests choose to exercise full MavenCli build execution rather than simple in-process/help/version paths, keep that isolated with temporary directories and avoid relying on the host ~/.m2, settings.xml, or network access.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Maven 2.0.7 is very old and some public/internal APIs differ from 2.0.6; generated tests must use the 2.0.7 constructor signatures.\",\n    \"Full Maven build execution can read local settings/repositories or attempt artifact resolution, so such integration-style tests may be flaky unless isolated in test code.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0004171a090db845016a41634461b08190904c80367abf4edc\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1029, "output": 784, "cacheRead": 26112, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27925, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782670135697, "responseId": "resp_0004171a090db845016a41633826748190a47a3ea93e1425f8"}}
